This topic describes how operators can view <%= vars.product_short %> pod usage information from Telemetry or the <%= vars.runtime_abbr %>billing database.

Operators use this data to
calculate billed usage, perform customer chargebacks, generate usage reports, and perform other functions.

## <a id="telemetry"></a><%= vars.runtime_abbr %> Telemetry

<%= vars.product_short %> Telemetry monitors deployment-wide pod consumption for billing, auditing, scaling, and other platform operations.
For more information, see [Telemetry](./telemetry.html).

## <a id="billing-db"></a><%= vars.runtime_abbr %> Billing Database

<p class="note"><strong>Deprecation Notice</strong>: With the <%= vars.product_short %> v1.9 release,
support for the billing database is scheduled to end, and the component will no longer record data.
Operators can instead use <a href="./telemetry.html">Telemetry</a><br>
Please reach out to <a href="mailto:pks-telemetry@groups.vmware.com">pks-telemetry@groups.vmware.com</a> if you are impacted by this deprecation.</p>

The <%= vars.product_short %> billing database stores the following pod usage data:

- **Watermark**: the number of pods that run at a single time.
- **Consumption**: the memory and CPU usage of pods.

### <a id="data"></a>Usage Data Format

This section describes the usage data records you can view in the <%= vars.product_short %> billing
database. The agent pod collects usage data for the deployment and sends the data
to the <%= vars.product_short %> aggregator agent. The aggregator agent then stores the data in the <%= vars.product_short %> billing database. You can access the billing database from the <%= vars.control_plane %> VM.

